d by [[Global Citizen (website)|Global Citizen]] in support of the [[World Health Organization]]. The special is intended to promote the practice of [[social distancing]] during the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.walesonline.co.uk/whats-on/music-nightlife-news/live-streamed-gigs-coronavirus-yungblud-17955670|title=The best live streamed gigs to watch at home during coronavirus|first=Laura|last=Clements|date=March 20, 2020|website=walesonline}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.globalcitizen.org/en/content/topics/together-at-home/|title=#TogetherAtHome|date=March 26, 2020|website=[[Global Citizen (website)|Global Citizen]]}}</ref><ref name=\"billboard\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9335531/coronavirus-quarantine-music-events-online-streams|title=Here Are All the Live Streams & Virtual Concerts to Watch During Coronavirus Crisis (Updating)|date=March 30, 2020|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dailyutahchronicle.com/2020/03/26/together-at-home/|title=\u2018Together At Home\u2019 Series Showcases Music\u2019s Limitless Abilities|date=March 26, 2020|website=[[The Daily Utah Chronicle]]}}</ref>\n\nOn April 18, 2020, a six-hour pre-show was streamed online immediately prior to the television global broadcast. The online portion of the event was hosted through [[YouTube]] by actress and presenter [[Jameela Jamil]] (first hour), actor [[Matthew McConaughey]] (second hour), actress [[Danai Gurira]] (third hour), singer [[Becky G]] (fourth hour), transgender actress [[Laverne Cox]] (fifth hour) and actor [[Don Cheadle]] (sixth hour). It featured many appearances from celebrities.\n\n==Participants of concert series==\n{{div col|colwidth=15em}}\n* [[Alex Gaskarth]]<ref name=alltimelow>{{Cite web|url=https://www.globalcitizen.org/en/content/all-time-low-together-at-home/|title=All Time Low\u2019s Frontman Plays Old Hits and New Album for \u2018Together At Home\u