[Victoria Beckham]]\n|Fashion designer and singer\n|-\n|[[Henry Golding]]\n|Actor\n|-\n|[[Ellen DeGeneres]]\n|Comedian and TV host\n|-\n|[[Savannah Guthrie]]\n|Host of ''[[Today (American TV program)|Today]]''\n|-\n|[[Hoda Kotb]]\n|Host of ''[[Today (American TV program)|Today]]''\n|-\n|[[Amy Poehler]]\n|Actress\n|-\n|[[Beyonc\u00e9]]\n|Singer\n|-\n|[[Tedros Adhanom]]\n|Director-General of the [[World Health Organization]]\n|-\n|[[LL Cool J]]\n|Singer\n|-\n|[[Shah Rukh Khan]]\n|Actor\n|-\n|[[Norah O'Donnell]]\n|Television journalist\n|-\n|[[Alicia Keys]]\n|Singer\n|-\n|[[Ant\u00f3nio Guterres]]\n|[[Secretary-General of the United Nations]]\n|-\n|[[Laura Bush]]\n|Former [[First Lady of the United States]]\n|-\n|[[Michelle Obama]]\n|Former [[First Lady of the United States]]\n|-\n|[[Lester Holt]]\n|Host of ''[[NBC Nightly News]]'' and ''[[Dateline NBC]]''\n|-\n|[[Melinda Gates]] and [[Bill Gates]]\n|Philanthropists and former general of [[Microsoft]]\n|-\n|[[David Ho]]\n|Doctor\n|-\n|[[Oprah Winfrey]]\n|TV host\n|-\n|[[Awkwafina]]\n|Actress\n|-\n|[[James Longman]]\n|Journalist\n|-\n|[[J Balvin]]\n|Singer\n|-\n|[[Priyanka Chopra|Priyanka Chopra Jonas]]\n|Actress\n|-\n|[[Kerry Washington]]\n|Actress\n|-\n|[[Idris Elba]] and his wife Sabrina\n|Actor\n|-\n|[[Gayle King]]\n|Broadcast journalist\n|-\n|[[Deborah Roberts]]\n|Television journalist\n|-\n|[[Amina J. Mohammed]]\n|Deputy Secretary-General of the United Nations\n|-\n|[[SpongeBob SquarePants (character)|SpongeBob SquarePants]]\n|Fictional character from ''[[SpongeBob SquarePants]]''\n|-\n|[[Pharrell Williams]]\n|Singer\n|-\n|[[Lupita Nyong'o]]\n|Actress\n|-\n|[[Oscar the Grouch]]\n|''[[Sesame Street]]'' fictional character\n|}\n\n===Broadcast===\nThe television special was broadcast on [[NBC]], [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]], and [[CBS]] in the [[United States]]. It was also aired on Spanish-language television network [[Univision]]. The special was also simulcast on networks owned by [[ViacomCBS]] ([[CMT (American TV channel)|CMT]], [[Comedy Central]], [[Logo TV]], [[MTV]], [[Nickelodeon]], [[Paramount Network]], [[Pop (American TV channel)|Pop]], [[TV Land]], and [[VH1]]),<ref name=\"viacom\">{{cite web|url=http://www.cmt.com/news/1820008/viacomcbs-networks-to-air-one-world-together-at-home-on-april-18/ |title=ViacomCBS Networks to Air ONE WORLD: TOGETHER AT HOME on April 18 |work=[[CMT (American TV channel)|CMT]] |date=April 7, 2020 |accessdate=April 9, 2020}}</ref> [[NBCUniversal]] ([[Bravo (American TV channel)|Bravo]], [[E!]], [[MSNBC]], [[NBCSN]], [[Syfy]], and [[USA Network]]),<ref name=\"variety\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/music/news/one-world-together-at-home-telecast-lady-gaga-paul-mccartney-lizzo-billie-eilish-global-citizen-who-1234571901/ |title=\u2018One World: Together at Home\u2019 Telecast Will Span Major Networks, Feature Lady Gaga, Paul McCartney, Lizzo, Billie Eilish, More |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=April 6, 2020 |accessdate=April 9, 2020}}</ref> [[Walt Disney Television]] ([[Freeform (TV channel)|Freeform]] and [[National Geographic (American TV channel)|National Geographic]]),<ref name=\"variety\" /> [[Katz Broadcasting]] ([[Bounce TV]] and [[Laff (TV network)|Laff]]),<ref name=\"globalcitizen\">{{cite web|url=https://www.globalcitizen.org/en/content/one-world-together-at-home-how-to-tune-in/|title=How You Can Tune Into \u2018One World: Together At Home\u2019 Wherever You Are in the World |work=[[Global Citizen (website)|Global Citizen]]|date=April 16, 2020|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}</ref> and on [[AXS TV]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.broadcastingcable.com/post-type-the-wire/axs-tv-broadcast-one-world-together-at-home-global-citizen-world-health-organization-jimmy-fallon-jimmy-kimmel-stephen-colbert |title=AXS TV to Broadcast 'One World: Together At Home,' Presented by Global Citizen & The World Health Organization, Airing Live & Commercial-Free on April 18 at 8 p.m. ET/5 p.m. PT |work=[[Broadcasting & Cable]] |date=April 8, 2020 |accessdate=April 9, 2020}}</ref> [[iHeartMedia]] also participated in the broadcast.\n\nIn the [[United Kingdom]], the BBC commissioned a Britain-centric broadcast of ''One World: Together at Home'' that aired on [[BBC One]] on Sunday 19 April at 7:15pm, presented by [[BBC Radio]] personalities [[Clara Amfo]], [[Claudia Winkleman]] and [[Dermot O'Leary]]. Produced for the BBC by [[Twofour]], it featured additional performances from the acts featured in the main special along with exclusive performances from UK acts such as [[Little Mix]] and interviews with, and surprises for, front line workers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/2020/owtah-presenters|title=BBC - Clara Amfo, Claudia Winkleman and Dermot O\u2019Leary to present BBC One coverage of One World: Together At Home - Media Centre|website=www.bbc.co.uk|date=16 April 2020|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n====International broadcasters====\n{{div col}}\n* Africa: [[BET International|BET]], [[Comedy Central#International|Comedy Central]], [[MTV Africa]], [[MTV Base (African TV channel)|MTV Base]] and [[Vuzu]]<ref name=\"globalcitizen\" />\n* Albania: [[Radio Televizioni Shqiptar|RTSH 2]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rtsh.al/lajme/together-at-home-koncerti-me-emrat-me-te-famshem-boteror-te-muzikes-sonte-ne-oren-18-30-ne-rtsh-2/|title=\u201cTogether At Home\u201d, koncerti me emrat m\u00eb t\u00eb famsh\u00ebm bot\u00ebror t\u00eb muzik\u00ebs, sonte n\u00eb or\u00ebn 18.30 n\u00eb RTSH 2|publisher=Radio Televizioni Shqiptar|date=19 April 2020}}</ref>\n* Argentina: [[Telefe]],<ref name=\"viacom\" /> [[Comedy Central (Latin America)|Comedy Central]], [[MTV (Latin America)|MTV]], [[MTV Hits (Latin America)|MTV Hits]], [[Paramount Channel]], [[VH1 (Latin America)|VH1]], [[VH1 HD]], [[VH1 MegaHits]], [[TNT (American TV network)#Latin America|TNT]], [[AXN]], [[Sony Channel (Latin American TV channel)|Sony Channel]] and National Geographic.\n* Australia: [[Network 