 TNT, AXN, and Sony Channel\n* Vietnam: K+ NS \n''Additional sources:'' GlobalCitizen.org<ref name=\"together\" />\n{{Div col end}}\n\n====Online streaming====\nThe special was also available on several digital platforms such as [[Alibaba Group|Alibaba]], [[Apple Inc.|Apple]], [[Facebook]], [[Instagram]], [[LiveXLive]], [[Prime Video]], [[Tencent]], [[Tencent Music]], [[Roblox]], [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]], [[TuneIn]], [[Twitch (service)|Twitch]], [[Twitter]], [[Yahoo!]], and [[YouTube]].<ref name=\"WHO\" />\n\n== Impact ==\n''One World: Together at Home'' spurred sales gains for the songs performed as part of the event. On April 18, 2020, the songs performed on the show sold more than 12,000 [[Music download|digital downloads]]\u2014a gain of 735% versus April 17, 2020. The most notable sellers from the two-hour television special were [[Taylor Swift]]'s \"[[Soon You'll Get Better]]\", [[Maluma (singer)|Maluma]]'s \"[[Carnaval (song)|Carnaval]]\" and [[Kacey Musgraves]]' \"[[Rainbow (Kacey Musgraves song)|Rainbow]]\", as they together accounted for 42% of the total song sales generated by the show. The songs performed during the pre-show broadcast generated 6,000 in sales\u2014up 75% from April 17, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9361488/one-world-together-at-home-concert-yields-sales-gains-for-taylor-swift-kacey-musgraves-more|title=\u2018One World: Together at Home\u2019 Concert Yields Sales Gains for Taylor Swift, Kacey Musgraves & More|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|date=2020-04-19|website=Billboard|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[iHeart Living Room Concert for America]]\n* [[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on the music industry]]\n* [[Live Aid]]\n* [[Saturday Night Seder]]\n\n==Notes and references==\n===Notes===\n{{Notelist}}\n\n===References===\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|https://www.globalcitizen.org/en/connect/togetherathome/}}\n\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States}}\n[[Category:2020 concerts]]\n[[Category:2020 television specials]]\n[[Category:March 2020 events in the United States]]\n[[Category:Music television specials]]\n[[Category:Responses to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Simulcasts]]\n[[Category:Benefit concerts]]\n[[Category:April 2020 events in the United States]]\n", "name_user": "90.204.78.250", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Together_at_Home"}
{"title_page": "Brooklyn Beckham", "text_new": "{{pp-pc|small=yes}}\n{{short description|English model and photographer}}\n{{use British English|date=August 2016}}\n{{Infobox model\n|name          = Brooklyn Beckham\n|occupation    = {{hlist |Model |photographer}}\n|years_active  = 2014{{ndash}}present\n|birth_name    = Brooklyn Joseph Beckham\n|birth_date  = {{birth date and age |1999|3|4|df=yes}}\n|birth_place   = [[West End of London|West End]], [[London]], England\n|nationality = [[British people|British]]\n|parents       = [[David Beckham]]<br>[[Victoria Beckham]]\n|relatives     = \n|haircolour    = Brown\n|eyecolour     = Brown\n}}\n'''Brooklyn Joseph Beckham''' (born 4 March 1999) is a British model and photographer.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/brooklyn-romeo-beckham-vogue-china|title=Brooklyn Beckham Just Scored His Biggest Vogue Cover Yet|first=Cond\u00e9|last=Nast|website=Teen Vogue}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2016/jul/13/brooklyn-beckham-burberry-campaign-art-critics-verdict|title=Brooklyn Beckham's Burberry campaign \u2013 the art critic's verdict|first=Jonathan|last=Jones|date=13 July 2016|publisher=|via=www.theguardian.com|newspaper=The Guardian}}</ref> He is the eldest son of former British footballer [[David Beckham]] and British singer-turned-fashion designer [[Victoria Beckham]].\n\n==Early life==\nBrooklyn Joseph Beckham was born at the [[Portland Hospital]] in West End of [[London]], the son of David Beckham and Victoria Beckham ([[n\u00e9e]] Adams). It is often reported that he was named Brooklyn because he was conceived in [[Brooklyn, New York]], but he was not; that is where his mother discovered she was pregnant and the place where David Beckham went after the [[1998 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120116072345/http://celebritybabies.people.com/2007/03/08/the_origin_of_b/|archive-date=January 6, 2012|url=http://celebritybabies.people.com/2007/03/08/the_origin_of_b/|title=The origin of Brooklyn Beckham's name|work=People}}</ref> He grew up in [[Madrid]], [[Spain]], while his father played for [[Real Madrid]] and in [[Los Angeles]], [[California]] when his father played for [[LA Galaxy]]. According to the elder Beckham, he and his younger brothers Romeo and Cruz learned to speak Spanish fluently, and had American accents while living in California. He has three younger siblings: Romeo James, Cruz David and sister Harper Seven. His godparents are [[Elton John]], [[David Furnish]], and [[Elizabeth Hurley]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hellomagazine.com/celebrities/2013112515798/celebrity-godparents-godchildren-famous/|title=Celebrity godparents and famous godchildren in pictures|date=25 November 2013|website=HELLO!}}</ref>\n\nTo earn money for his own things, he worked part time at a coffee shop.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://metro.co.uk/2014/05/19/its-barista-beckham-brooklyn-beckham-gets-weekend-job-in-west-london-coffee-shop-4732858/|title=Guess which Beckham has got a job paying \u00a32.68 an hour|date=19 May 2014|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nBeckham formerly played in the [[Arsenal F.C. Academy]]; he left because he did not receive a scholarship by Arsenal Football Academy who preferred two other prospects at his position.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/david-beckham-son-brooklyn-football-2015-9|title=David Beckham's oldest son no longer wants to play soccer, and the reason why broke his dad's heart|first=Cork|last=Gaines|website=Business Insider}}</ref>\n\nHe started modelling in 2014,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/526717/brooklyn-beckham-makes-modeling-debut-on-man-about-town-magazine-see-the-pics|title=Brooklyn Beckham Makes Modeling Debut on Man About Town Magazin|date=31 March 2014|website=E! Online}}</ref> and has appeared in editorials and covers for ''[[Vogue China]]'', ''[[Vogue (British magazine)|Miss Vogue]]'', ''[[Interview (magazine)|Interview]]'', ''[[L'Uomo Vogue]]'', ''[[The New York Times|T:The New York Times Style Magazine]]'', and ''[[Dazed]] Korea''. He has been photographed by [[Bruce Weber (photographer)|Bruce Weber]], [[Terry Richardson]], Daniel Jackson, and [[Alasdair McLellan]]. Beckham himself photographed a campaign for [[Burberry]] BRIT, starring models Ben Rees, Carvell Conduah, Eliza Thomas, Liv Mason Pearson, and Maddie Demaine.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fashionista.com/2016/07/brooklyn-beckham-burberry-fragrance|title=BROOKLYN BECKHAM'S FRAGRANCE CAMPAIGN FOR BURBERRY IS HERE|work=Fashionista}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://models.com/work/burberry-prorsum-brit-fragrance|title=Brit Fragrance 2016 (Burberry)|website=MODELS.com}}</ref>\n\nHe is a part of a modelling trend where children of famous people and models with large social media presence are successful.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://models.com/oftheminute/?p=80347|title=Moments of the Year: 6. Celebrity Kin|work=models.com}}</ref> He has a strong following of Chinese fans; he has been the face of [[Huawei]] Honor 8 Android phones alongside [[Scarlett Johansson]], [[Karlie Kloss]], and [[Henry Cavill]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/technology-37106220|title=Why is Brooklyn Beckham selling phones?|first=Rhiannon|last=Williams|date=17 August 2016|publisher=|via=www.bbc.com|work=BBC News}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nBeckham previously dated American actress [[Chlo\u00eb Grace Moretz]] and French model-singer [[Sonia Ben Ammar]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/celebrity/chloe-grace-moretz-confirms-shes-dating-brooklyn-beckham/|title=WATCH: Chlo&#235; Grace Moretz Confirms She's Dating Brooklyn Beckham: 'Yes, We're in a Relationship'|website=PEOPLE.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/fashion/people/everything-you-need-to-know-about-brooklyn-beckhams-girlfriend-s/|title=Everything you need to know about Brooklyn Beckham's 'girlfriend' Sonia Ben Ammar|first1=Emma|last1=Spedding|first2=Bibby|last2=Sowray|date=14 March 2016|newspaper=Telegraph}}</ref> He attended the [[2016 Democratic National Convention]] with Moretz in support of [[Hillary Clinton]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/news/a38186/chloe-grace-moretz-brooklyn-beckham-dnc/|title=Chlo\u00eb Grace Moretz Had Best Date Ever at the Democratic National Convention|first=Kristina|last=Rodulfo|date=29 July 2016|website=ELLE}}</ref>\nHe began dating American actress [[Nicola  Peltz]] since November 2019.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Beckham, Brooklyn}}\n[[Category:1999 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:English male models]]\n[[Category:English photographers]]\n[[Category:English expatriates in the United States]]\n[[Category:Parsons School of Design alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-pc|small=yes}}\n{{short description|English model and photographer}}\n{{use British English|date=August 2016}}\n{{Infobox model\n|name          = Brooklyn Beckham\n|occupation    = {{hlist |Model |photographer}}\n|years_active  = 2014{{ndash}}present\n|birth_name    = Brooklyn Joseph Beckham\n|birth_date  = {{birth date and age |1999|3|4|df=yes}}\n|birth_place   = [[West End of London|West End]], [[London]], England\n|nationality = [[British people|British]]\n|parents       = [[David Beckham]]<br>[[Victoria Beckham]]\n|relatives     = \n|haircolour    = Brown\n|eyecolour     = Brown\n}}\n'''Brooklyn Joseph Beckham''' (born 4 March 1999) is a British model and photographer.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/brooklyn-romeo-beckham-vogue-china|title=Brooklyn Beckham Just Scored His Biggest Vogue Cover Yet|first=Cond\u00e9|last=Nast|website=Teen Vogue}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2016/jul/13/brooklyn-beckham-burberry-campaign-art-critics-verdict|title=Brooklyn Beckham's Burberry campaign \u2013 the art critic's verdict|first=Jonathan|last=Jones|date=13 July 2016|publisher=|via=www.theguardian.com|newspaper=The Guardia